children.remarks:
When option aliasing is disabled, the parser will resolve options using only the . When option aliasing is enabled, the parser will recognize and resolve options using:

  • Short NameShort option or alias prefixed by one (e.g., -a).
  • Long NameLong option prefixed by two (e.g., --all).
  • Hybrid NameHybrid option with both short and long option naming (e.g., --long-name).
children.summary: Indicates whether option aliasing is disabled. Defaults to false.

children.remarks: The is required and cannot be null or consist only of whitespace.
children.summary: Specifies the prefix used for options. Defaults to -.

children.remarks: The option value separator must be a single Unicode character, and it can be a single whitespace.
children.summary: Gets or sets the option value separator. Defaults to .
Gets or sets the temporary runtime separator that is used to optimize the parsing algorithm. Defaults to 0x1F or Unit Separator.

children.remarks: The command string separator must be a single Unicode character, and it can be a whitespace character.
children.summary: Gets or sets the command string separator. Defaults to a single whitespace.
Gets or sets the value delimiter used to extract a value within the configured delimiter. Defaults to ".
